<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="85" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85">
Body (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Alopecosa disca Peng, Yin, Zhang &amp; Kim, 1997, female. A Habitus, dorsal view B eyes, front view C chelicera, ventral view D sternum, ventral view E epigyne F vulva G vulva, showing the detailed left half H vulva, moved slightly from the normal ventral view I vulva, showing the detailed right half. Abbreviations: Ag accessorial gland, Cd copulatory duct, Sb septal base, Sp spermatheca, Ss septal stalk. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B, D); 0.5 mm (C); 0.1 mm (E-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.945.52287.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/428129" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">1A</figureCitation>
) length 16.0, carapace 7.9 long, 5.0 wide, abdomen 8.8 long, 5.8 wide (data from original description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yin, CM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Lanzhou University Natural Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" refId="B17" refString="Yin, CM, Peng, XJ, Xie, LP, Bao, YH, Wang, JF, 1997. Lycosids in China (Arachnida: Araneae). Hunan Normal University Press, 317 pp. [in Chinese]" title="Lycosids in China (Arachnida: Araneae). Hunan Normal University Press, 317 pp. [in Chinese]" year="1997">Yin et al. 1997</bibRefCitation>
: 64). Carapace dark reddish brown. Cervical and radial grooves distinct, darker than body color. Fovea linear, short, but a little thick. Head region wide, with anterior margin almost 4/5 width of thorax region. Anterior eye row straight, almost as wide as median one, posterior row widest. Eye sizes and inter-distances (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Alopecosa disca Peng, Yin, Zhang &amp; Kim, 1997, female. A Habitus, dorsal view B eyes, front view C chelicera, ventral view D sternum, ventral view E epigyne F vulva G vulva, showing the detailed left half H vulva, moved slightly from the normal ventral view I vulva, showing the detailed right half. Abbreviations: Ag accessorial gland, Cd copulatory duct, Sb septal base, Sp spermatheca, Ss septal stalk. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B, D); 0.5 mm (C); 0.1 mm (E-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.945.52287.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/428129" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">1A, B</figureCitation>
): AME 0.30, ALE 0.27, PME 0.49, PLE 0.47; AME-AME 0.19, AME-ALE 0.2, PME-PME 0.49, PME-PLE 0.67. Clypeus height 0.23. Chelicerae black-brown, with three promarginal and two retromarginal teeth (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Alopecosa disca Peng, Yin, Zhang &amp; Kim, 1997, female. A Habitus, dorsal view B eyes, front view C chelicera, ventral view D sternum, ventral view E epigyne F vulva G vulva, showing the detailed left half H vulva, moved slightly from the normal ventral view I vulva, showing the detailed right half. Abbreviations: Ag accessorial gland, Cd copulatory duct, Sb septal base, Sp spermatheca, Ss septal stalk. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B, D); 0.5 mm (C); 0.1 mm (E-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.945.52287.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/428129" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">1C</figureCitation>
). Both labium and endites black brown, with reddish brown distal parts. Sternum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Alopecosa disca Peng, Yin, Zhang &amp; Kim, 1997, female. A Habitus, dorsal view B eyes, front view C chelicera, ventral view D sternum, ventral view E epigyne F vulva G vulva, showing the detailed left half H vulva, moved slightly from the normal ventral view I vulva, showing the detailed right half. Abbreviations: Ag accessorial gland, Cd copulatory duct, Sb septal base, Sp spermatheca, Ss septal stalk. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B, D); 0.5 mm (C); 0.1 mm (E-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.945.52287.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/428129" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">1D</figureCitation>
) brown, with metallic luster. STL 3.52, STW 2.82 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Alopecosa disca Peng, Yin, Zhang &amp; Kim, 1997, female. A Habitus, dorsal view B eyes, front view C chelicera, ventral view D sternum, ventral view E epigyne F vulva G vulva, showing the detailed left half H vulva, moved slightly from the normal ventral view I vulva, showing the detailed right half. Abbreviations: Ag accessorial gland, Cd copulatory duct, Sb septal base, Sp spermatheca, Ss septal stalk. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B, D); 0.5 mm (C); 0.1 mm (E-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.945.52287.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/428129" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">1D</figureCitation>
). Palp and legs reddish brown, robust, without any distinct annuli. Leg measurements: I 18.30 (5.00, 6.60, 3.80, 2.90); II 16.70 (4.80, 5.80, 3.60, 2.50); III 15.00 (4.50, 5.00, 3.60, 1.90); IV 20.40 (6.10, 7.00, 5.00, 2.30) (data from original description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yin, CM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Lanzhou University Natural Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="85" refId="B17" refString="Yin, CM, Peng, XJ, Xie, LP, Bao, YH, Wang, JF, 1997. Lycosids in China (Arachnida: Araneae). Hunan Normal University Press, 317 pp. [in Chinese]" title="Lycosids in China (Arachnida: Araneae). Hunan Normal University Press, 317 pp. [in Chinese]" year="1997">Yin et al. 1997</bibRefCitation>
: 64), leg formula 4123. Dorsum of abdomen (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Alopecosa disca Peng, Yin, Zhang &amp; Kim, 1997, female. A Habitus, dorsal view B eyes, front view C chelicera, ventral view D sternum, ventral view E epigyne F vulva G vulva, showing the detailed left half H vulva, moved slightly from the normal ventral view I vulva, showing the detailed right half. Abbreviations: Ag accessorial gland, Cd copulatory duct, Sb septal base, Sp spermatheca, Ss septal stalk. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B, D); 0.5 mm (C); 0.1 mm (E-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.945.52287.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/428129" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">1A</figureCitation>
) dark brown mixed yellowish brown. Cardiac mark distinct, dark brown and large. Posterior half of abdomen with 4 or 5 chevrons (because the type specimen has been wrinkled, chevron patterns showed in color photos of the present paper are not clearer than those showed in line drawings of the original paper). Venter of abdomen grey yellowish in the middle and dark grey laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="85">
Epigyne (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Alopecosa disca Peng, Yin, Zhang &amp; Kim, 1997, female. A Habitus, dorsal view B eyes, front view C chelicera, ventral view D sternum, ventral view E epigyne F vulva G vulva, showing the detailed left half H vulva, moved slightly from the normal ventral view I vulva, showing the detailed right half. Abbreviations: Ag accessorial gland, Cd copulatory duct, Sb septal base, Sp spermatheca, Ss septal stalk. Scale bars: 1 mm (A, B, D); 0.5 mm (C); 0.1 mm (E-I)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.945.52287.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/428129" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">1E-I</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Alopecosa disca Peng, Yin, Zhang &amp; Kim, 1997, female. A Epigyne B vulva C vulva, showing the detailed left half D vulva, showing the detailed right half. Abbreviations: Ag accessorial gland, Cd copulatory duct, Fd fertilization duct, Sb septal base, Sp spermatheca, Ss septal stalk. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (A-D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.945.52287.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/428130" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">2</figureCitation>
) wider than long. Atrium and anterior hood absent. Septum weakly sclerotized, with short stem (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">Ss</emphasis>
) and broad base (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">Sb</emphasis>
); stem shorter than base height. Spermathecae with clavate head, slender and curved stalk, and accessorial gland (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="85">Ag</emphasis>
) situated at the place near copulatory duct. Copulatory ducts short, slightly twisted.
</paragraph>
